  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In this letter, William Lloyd Garrison introduces Mrs. Eliza Frances Jackson Meriam Eddy to Elizabeth Pease. He commends Mrs. Eddy&apos;s anti-slavery activities and Mr. Eddy&apos;s liberal contributions to the American Anti-Slavery Society. Garrison believes the cause of emancipation is &quot;advancing mightily, and we are rejoicing in hope.&quot; Garrison&apos;s health has improved through the water cure. Henry C. Wright is still in Ohio.</subfield>
